    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture of a group of three closely related Algonkian-speaking Indian tribes in Alberta and Montana, comprising the Pikuni, or Piegan, the Kainah, or Blood, and the Siksika, or Blackfoot proper (often referred to as the Northern Blackfoot). Not to be confused with the Sihasapa, another Plains Indian tribe that is also referred to as Blackfoot.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refiérase a la cultura de un grupo de tres tribus indias de Algonkian, relacionadas en Alberta y Montana. No ser confundido con Sihasapa, otra tribu del indio de llanos que también se refieren como Blackfoot.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de cultuur van een groep van drie nauw verwante Algonkian-sprekende Indiaanse stammen in Alberta en Montana: de Pikuni (of Piegan), de Kainah (of Blood) en de Siksika (de eigenlijke Blackfoot, vaak de Noordelijke Blackfoot genoemd). Niet te verwarren met de Sihasapa, een andere stam van prairie-indianen die ook Blackfoot wordt genoemd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指三個與分佈於加拿大亞伯達省與美國蒙大拿州地區之阿爾根金語系印地安部族關連緊密的族群，包括皮堀尼克族（Pikuni）或稱皮埃甘族（Piegan）、凱納族（Kainah）或稱布盧德族（Blood）、西克西洽族（Siksika）或稱正統黑腳族（Blackfoot proper）（通常也被稱作北部黑腳族）。勿與另一支也被稱作黑腳族的大平原印第安部族西哈薩帕族（Sihasapa）混淆。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
